---
description: Coding conventions for frontend files.
globs: ["**/*.tsx", "**/*.ts"]
alwaysApply: false
---

- Functional components only, with TypeScript props interfaces (no `any`).
- Co-locate component-specific types in the same file unless shared across multiple components (then src/types/).
- Use existing hooks/utilities (check src/hooks/, src/lib/) before writing new ones.
- Absolute imports via configured path aliases (@/components, @/lib), not deep relative paths.
- No new dependencies without flagging it in the summary — don't silently add packages.
- One component per file, small and focused. Split when a file exceeds ~150-200 lines or handles more than one concern.